
@startuml

class GasStation {
  -id: int
  -address: string
  -fuelPumps: List<FuelPump>
}

class FuelPump {
  -id: int
  -pumpNumber: int
  -isSelfService: boolean
  -fuels: List<Fuel>
}

class Fuel {
  -name: string
  -octaneRating: float
}

class DailyPrice {
  -date: Date
  -fuel: Fuel
  -gasStation: GasStation
  -pricePerLiter: float
}

class FuelPurchase {
  -id: int
  -fuelPump: FuelPump
  -fuel: Fuel
  -dailyPrice: DailyPrice
  -litersDispensed: float
}

GasStation "1" -- "0..*" FuelPump : has
FuelPump "1" -- "0..*" Fuel : offers
Fuel "1" -- "0..*" DailyPrice : applies to
GasStation "1" -- "0..*" DailyPrice : has
FuelPump "1" -- "0..*" FuelPurchase : has
Fuel "1" -- "0..*" FuelPurchase : purchased
DailyPrice "1" -- "0..*" FuelPurchase : applies to

@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- **GasStation** has multiple **FuelPumps**.
- Each **FuelPump** can offer multiple **Fuels**.
- A **Fuel** can have multiple **DailyPrices** (one per day and gas station).
- A **FuelPurchase** is associated with one **FuelPump**, one **Fuel**, and one **DailyPrice**.

